High Rise is the first studio EP by the American rock band Stone Temple Pilots, released on October 8, 2013 through 13Star Records. It is the first release by the band to not feature former lead vocalist Scott Weiland, who was fired from the band in February 2013. It instead features his singing replacement Chester Bennington of the Linkin Park and Dead by Sunrise fame, and the band are credited on the EP as Stone Temple Pilots with Chester Bennington. The whole album can now be heard on Spotify, Pandora Radio, and Slackerz Radio. It can be purchased on iTunes, and on Amazon in digital download and in compact disc.
